E8 reclassification (2026-05-24): the original framing — "ClearKeptObjects
never runs" — was wrong.  ClearKeptObjects DOES run; the FinalizationRegistry
callback fires (`finalized:A` is emitted).  The bug is that `process.exit(0)`
inside the finalizer callback doesn't terminate `_start` before the surviving
`setTimeout(200)` fires.  Likely root cause: finalizer runs in microtask
context where the exit throws but `_start` has already returned past that
frame.  See experiments/e8-microtask-pump-spike/FINDINGS.md.

Still skipped pending a separate investigation of process.exit semantics
inside FinalizationRegistry callbacks.  GC observation is non-deterministic
— even once the exit bug is fixed this test may be flaky without --expose-gc.
